    public interface JsonUrlIterator
extends ExceptionProvider
    An JSON→URL iterator provides streaming (e.g. forward, read-only) access to parsed JSON→URL text as a sequence of one or more events.

    Options will affect what events are returned. In some cases combinations of options could reasonably result in more than one event. The table below addresses these ambiguities.

    OptionsNotes
    IMPLIED_STRING_LITERALS + EMPTY_UNQUOTED_VALUE When both flags are present then the grammar allows for either VALUE_STRING or VALUE_EMPTY_LITERAL. In this case the implied string option takes precedence and VALUE_STRING is returned.
    IMPLIED_STRING_LITERALS + AQF When both flags are present then the grammar allows for either VALUE_STRING or VALUE_EMPTY_LITERAL. In this case the implied string option takes precedence and VALUE_STRING is returned.
